# Smart Home System

A Java console-based smart home simulation created for the Advanced Programming assignment. The application allows users to control virtual smart devices through a menu-driven interface. Users can view device status, turn devices on or off, and adjust thermostat temperature settings. The project demonstrates object-oriented programming principles including inheritance, encapsulation, polymorphism, and abstraction, alongside the implementation of the Factory Pattern and Command Pattern.

## Running the Program

Java JDK must be installed before running the application. To check Java is installed, run `java --version` and `javac --version` in the terminal or command prompt.

### macOS

Open Terminal, move into the project folder using `cd SmartHomeSystem`, compile the program using `javac *.java`, then run the application using `java Main`.

### Windows

Open Command Prompt or PowerShell, move into the project folder using `cd SmartHomeSystem`, compile the program using `javac *.java`, then run the application using `java Main`.

### Linux

Open Terminal, move into the project folder using `cd SmartHomeSystem`, compile the program using `javac *.java`, then run the application using `java Main`.

